				\begin{document}$${\text{MSE}} = \frac{1}{n}\mathop \sum \limits_{i = 1}^{n} e_{i}^{2} .$$\end{document}The MAE and the MSE values range between one and zero as well. The closer their values to zero, the better competency in prediction the model has.
